<br />
you are a tool, you can sit in an air tight compact car.. say a neon for example, this neon could be completly air tight, you could have 4 people in this car (dont think you can fit anymore in a neon) driver sparks a joint, passenger sparks a joint, kid sittin back left or right sparks up a bowl. everybody finishes. damn cant see a dang thing. ask the kid that didnt participate, hey man are you high, nope.<br />
<br />
its known that when you smoke marijuana, THC (ya know the stuff that gets you high, tard) is much heavier than the smoke itself, and it instantly drops to the ground, or to your lungs, wherever the smoke is going origionally. this kid would not get high unless you physically took a big ass hit, held it in your mouth, and blew it all into his mouth for him to inhale.<br />
<br />
Trazier made a lot of good points, as did Reapin. Our country is free, but only a little. there are countries out there that have more freedom than us, of course sure were nearly the biggest, were the toughest, were the richest, i wonder how that came to be, not because we provided little freedom, because our United States background is made from Great Hero's, Scandalous businessmen, and slavery. We made ourselves the best by being an Imperialist country, jumping in every trade route, and war we could.<br />
<br />
Now the fact people get arrested for smoking, possessing or selling marijuana is ridiculous. Selling marijuana i can 100% agree it can get dangerous with the wrong crowd of people. Jails are very sadly over-crowded, by legalizing marijuana tax payers wouldnt be paying the assload of money they do to keep these people fed, clean, and alive in jail. legalizing cannibus would clear the jail problem, of course i think there should be some regulations such as, how much you smoke a day, quality, age, and so on. the only way for it to work would be like that, everybody knows so.<br />
 <br />
should it be legalized? sure, government should make 10% 20% 30% 40% 50% THC marijuana (as we all know cannibus doesnt contain but 20-30% thc, danks go up to the 40-50% range) offer to sell them in packs either like what we buy now, joint, dime, 20, quad, half, oz, qp, and so on.. or like Trazier said, like ciggaretts.<br />
<br />
But the thing that should be said is that no matter the consequences, weather it is legalized or not, people will still smoke weed, they will still sell it, weather the government would like to tax, and sell it to make hella cash. lay down some restrictions and make for a more or less happier country, then so be it.</font></p>
             
